        <h1>Pickpocketing</h1>
      <img src="/pickpocketSpain.jpg" alt="pickpockets" class="smaller-image">
      <p>
        Pickpocketing is unfortunately a common issue in certain tourist-dense areas of Spain, particularly in cities like Barcelona and Madrid. While Spain overall is a safe country for travelers, the prevalence of pickpockets in bustling urban centers is a concern that demands traveler awareness. 
        These opportunistic thieves tend to target crowded places where tourists gather, including busy streets, public transportation, popular attractions, and even restaurants. They often work in groups or pairs, with one creating a distraction while another swiftly snatches belongings.
