      </p>
    <a href="#" class="read-more">Read Full Post</a>
    <div class="full-content">
      <p>Utilize bags with secure closures that can be worn across your body, keeping your bag in front of you and well-guarded. Avoid displaying valuable items like cameras and electronics openly, as this can attract unwanted attention.
        To minimize the impact of theft, distribute your money, passport, and other essentials across different pockets or concealed pouches.
        When in your accommodation, make use of the hotel safe to store valuable items securely. Stay cautious when encountering unexpected distractions, such as someone bumping into you or seeking directions abruptly. These diversionary tactics are frequently used by pickpockets to create opportunities for theft.
      </p>
    </div>
